Local Path: This path uses a backslash \ Remote Path: This path uses a forward slash / -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Folder Transfer: We are able to transfer an entire folder and its contents.
Example...
C:\folderName -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- File Transfer: When specifying which file/files you want to move. You have the ability to use file masks/expressions to perform more complex transfer scenarios.
Examples...
* Matches any number (including zero) of arbitrary characters. *.doc (Will transfer all files with a doc exstension) *.* (Will transfer all files in a directory)
? Matches exactly one arbitrary character. photo????.png
[abc] Matches one character from set index_[abc].html
[a-z] Matches one charcter from the range index_[a-z].html
For a more examples and a through explination of this feature check out the link below. https://winscp.net/eng/docs/file_mask ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Logging: Two log files are generated at the end of a transfer/attempted transfer. One of these files (Formatted_FTP_Log_YYYYMM) contains select information about the transfer. Any failures and their messages will be logged into the file. This file is formatted to be accessible to ETL. Its formatting is...
DTS|TransferType|Protocol|Filename|Destination|Result
The second file (Standard_FTP_Log_YYYYMM) is generated by WinSCP each time a transfer/attempted transfer occurs. This log file is much more verbose than the formatted log and better suited for learning details about an individual transfer.
Both logs will append the newest transfer data. The log name is SET BY THE APPLICATION AND CANNOT BE CHANGED in the task editor. New logs will generated each month.
